            <p>Hand made jewellery is made even to this date. The Karigars as they are known in India make an entire piece of jewellery by hand with little help from modern day techniques, 
            the perfect amalgamation of the old and the new. 
            They sit patiently moulding each gold bar from a bar to the final form by constantly heating and cooling, which gradually gives shape to the metal.</p>
